President Trump delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House addressing the deadly shooting at Santa Fe High School in Texas. He expressed sadness and heartbreak over the incident and pledged to do everything in his power to protect students and keep weapons out of the hands of those who pose a threat. The President also discussed the issue of prison reform and the importance of helping former inmates find jobs and successfully reintegrate into society. He called for expanding prison work programs, increasing mental health services, and developing more effective drug treatment. President Trump urged Congress to pass legislation on prison reform and promised to sign a strong bill into law. He emphasized the belief in redemption and second chances and stated that America will be safer and stronger by giving former prisoners the opportunity to succeed.